library(tidyverse)
library(usmap)
library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)
library(stringr)
library(modelsummary)
library(jtools)
library(tidyr)
library(doBy)
library(RColorBrewer)
library(cowplot)


setwd("/Users/chris/Documents/MBMI/BMIN 503/BMIN503_Final_Project/")
dartmouth<-read.csv("county_medutil_6599ffs.csv", header=TRUE)
election<-read.csv("countypres_2000-2016.csv", header=TRUE)
cty_rank_2012<-read.csv("analytic_data2012.csv", header=TRUE, skip=1, sep=",")
cty_rank_2016<-read.csv("analytic_data2016.csv", header=TRUE, skip=1, sep=",")
rural_atlas_people<-read.csv("people.csv", header=TRUE)
rural_atlas_income<-read.csv("income.csv", header=TRUE)
gdp<-read.csv("gdp_bea_county_12_16.csv", header=TRUE, skip=4)

surg_dis<-dartmouth %>%
  filter(Eventname %in% c("AS_DIS"), Year %in% c(2011,2015), Race=="Overall", Gender=="All") %>%
  dplyr::select(Geo_Code, Adjusted_Rate, Crude_rate, Year) %>%
  rename(fips=Geo_Code, adj_surg_rate=Adjusted_Rate, crude_surg_rate=Crude_rate, surg_year=Year) %>%
  mutate(fips=str_pad(fips, 5, pad = "0"), adj_surg_rate=round(adj_surg_rate,digits=1), crude_surg_rate=round(crude_surg_rate,digits=1), merge_year=ifelse(surg_year==2011,2012,2016)) %>%
  filter(adj_surg_rate>=0)

elect_tmp<-election %>%
  filter(year %in% c(2008,2012,2016), party %in% c("republican","democrat"), !is.na(FIPS), !is.na(candidatevotes)) %>%
  select(FIPS, party, candidatevotes, year) %>%
  rename(fips=FIPS) %>%
  spread(party, candidatevotes) %>%
  mutate(fips=str_pad(fips, 5, pad = "0"), r_pct=republican/(republican+democrat)) %>%
  select(fips,year,r_pct)

elect_2012<-elect_tmp %>%
  filter(year %in% c(2008,2012)) %>%
  spread(year, r_pct) %>%
  rename(past_vote_share="2008", r_pct="2012") %>%
  mutate(elect_year=2012, merge_year=2012, past_vote_share=round(past_vote_share*100,digits=1), r_pct=round(r_pct*100,digits=1))

elect_2016<-elect_tmp %>%
  filter(year %in% c(2012,2016)) %>%
  spread(year, r_pct) %>%
  rename(past_vote_share="2012", r_pct="2016") %>%
  mutate(elect_year=2016, merge_year=2016, past_vote_share=round(past_vote_share*100,digits=1), r_pct=round(r_pct*100,digits=1))

elect_final<-rbind(elect_2012,elect_2016)

cty_rank_all<-dplyr::bind_rows(cty_rank_2012, cty_rank_2016)

cty_rank_all_clean<-cty_rank_all %>%
  mutate(fipscode=as.character(fipscode),
         fips=str_pad(fipscode, 5, pad = "0"),
         v002_rawvalue=v002_rawvalue*100,
         v021_rawvalue=v021_rawvalue*100,
         v023_rawvalue=v023_rawvalue*100,
         v054_rawvalue=v054_rawvalue*100,
         v058_rawvalue=v058_rawvalue*100,
         v085_rawvalue=v085_rawvalue*100,
         v051_rawvalue=round(v051_rawvalue,digits=0),
         v063_rawvalue=round(v063_rawvalue,digits=0),
         cty_year=year) %>%
  rename(pct_fairpoor=v002_rawvalue,
         pct_hsgrad=v021_rawvalue, 
         pct_unemp=v023_rawvalue,
         pct_nhblack=v054_rawvalue,
         pct_rural=v058_rawvalue,
         pct_uninsured=v085_rawvalue,
         tot_pop=v051_rawvalue,
         med_income=v063_rawvalue,
         merge_year=year) %>%
  dplyr::select(fips, pct_fairpoor, pct_hsgrad, pct_unemp, pct_nhblack, pct_rural, pct_uninsured, tot_pop, med_income, cty_year, merge_year)
  
rural_atlas_people_clean<-rural_atlas_people %>%
  mutate(fips=str_pad(FIPS, 5, pad = "0")) %>%
  dplyr::select(fips,PopDensity2010)

rural_atlas_income_clean<-rural_atlas_income %>%
  mutate(fips=str_pad(FIPS, 5, pad = "0")) %>%
  dplyr::select(fips, PovertyAllAgesPct)

gdp_clean<-gdp %>%
  rename(fips=GeoFips,y2012=X2011.2012, y2016=X2015.2016) %>%
  gather(year, pct_gdp_chg, y2012:y2016, factor_key=TRUE) %>%
  mutate(merge_year=ifelse(year=="y2012",2012,2016), pct_gdp_chg=as.numeric(pct_gdp_chg)) %>%
  dplyr::select(fips,merge_year,pct_gdp_chg) %>%
  filter(!is.na(pct_gdp_chg))

analytical_cohort<-surg_dis %>%
  left_join(elect_final) %>%
  left_join(cty_rank_all_clean) %>%
  left_join(rural_atlas_people_clean) %>%
  left_join(rural_atlas_income_clean) %>%
  left_join(gdp_clean) %>%
  mutate(merge_year=as.factor(merge_year), log_pop=log(tot_pop), log_med_inc=log(med_income))

collapse1 <- summaryBy(r_pct + adj_surg_rate + tot_pop ~ fips, FUN=c(mean), data=analytical_cohort)
collapse1<- collapse1 %>% mutate(log_adj_surg_rate=log(adj_surg_rate.mean))

usplot_surg<-plot_usmap(data=collapse1, values="adj_surg_rate.mean", regions = "counties", exclude=c("HI","AK")) + 
  labs(title = "Adjusted Rate of Surgical Discharges per 100K Medicare Enrollees by US County", subtitle="(Mean of 2012 & 2016)") + 
  theme(panel.background = element_rect(color=NA, fill = "white"), plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5), plot.subtitle=element_text(hjust=0.5)) + 
  scale_fill_gradient2(low="#2E74C0", mid="#D3D3D3", high="#CB454A",midpoint=81.55, name="Rate", na.value="white")

usplot_elect<-plot_usmap(data=collapse1, values="r_pct.mean", regions = "counties", exclude=c("HI","AK")) +
  labs(title = "Republican Voting % in the 2012 & 2016 Presidential Elections by County") +
  theme(panel.background = element_rect(color=NA, fill = "white"), plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5)) +
  scale_fill_gradient2(low="#2E74C0", mid="#D3D3D3", high="#CB454A", midpoint=50, name="Republican %", na.value="white")

usplot_surg

usplot_elect
